INTROS = {
  1 => <<~TXT,
    Naked and Afraid's first season aired between June 23 and July 28, 2013, launching Discovery Channel's flagship survival series across six standalone episodes. Each week sent a new pair of strangers into a different environment for a scheduled 21-day challenge — Costa Rican rainforest in the premiere "The Jungle Curse," the Tanzanian savanna, a Maldives sandbar, Panama's Caribbean coast, Malaysian Borneo, and finally the Louisiana bayou for "Beware the Bayou."

    The debut season introduced twelve survivalists who would go on to shape the franchise. Ky Furneaux, Laura Zerra, EJ Snyder, and Kellie Nightlinger all made their first appearance here, alongside Alison Teal, Puma Cabra, Shane Lewis, and Kim Shelton. The season established every convention that later editions inherited: the naked-and-afraid drop-in, the PSR (Primitive Survival Rating), the partner conflict arc, and the 21-day extraction ritual.
  TXT

  2 => <<~TXT,
    Season 2 aired from December 2013 through April 2014 across seven episodes, expanding the cast to eighteen survivalists. Filming spanned Panama for the premiere "Double Jeopardy," Madagascar, Fiji, Belize, Malaysia, Bolivia, and Peru — introducing "Man vs. Amazon" as the show's first Peruvian rainforest challenge and closing with the high-altitude "Meltdown in Bolivia," which pushed the format beyond humid jungle into thin air and cold.

    The run introduced Jeff Zausch, Forrest Galante, Manu Toigo, Cassie DePecol, Eva Rupert, and Fernando Calderon — several of whom would become long-running franchise faces. EJ Snyder returned from Season 1 for "Damned in Africa" in Madagascar, and Laura Zerra came back for Peru. The season's Belize entry "Mayan Misery" and Malaysian follow-up "The Pain Forest" locked in the show's early template of pairing tropical extremes with rapid mental unraveling.
  TXT

  3 => <<~TXT,
    Season 3 aired between June and October 2014 across ten episodes, the first double-length run in the franchise's history. Locations spanned Namibia for the premiere "Primal Fear," the Bahamas, Cambodia, Nicaragua, Argentina, Dominica, India's Himalayan foothills, Botswana, and Brazil — the widest geographic range of any Naked and Afraid season to that point.

    Standout entries include "Blood in the Water" (the show's first Bahamas challenge), "Himalayan Hell" filmed at altitude in India, and the desert-set finale "Dunes of Despair" in Brazil. The season introduced Hakim Isler, Honora Bowen, Tom McElroy, Chris Fischer, and Lindsey Leitelt — a cohort that helped set the tone for the franchise's mid-decade run. The Amazon and Cambodian jungle episodes established the visual template Discovery would carry through the following seasons.
  TXT

